.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "2023-12-19" "version 1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.br
echo "command" | ./simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell is a simple UNIX command interpreter that replicates functionalities of the standard shell. It was developed as a part of the Holberton School curriculum.
.PP
This shell can execute commands read from the standard input.
.SH FEATURES
Simple Shell features include:
.IP \[bu] 2
Running in interactive and non-interactive mode.
.IP \[bu] 2
Executing commands in PATH.
.IP \[bu] 2
Handling built-in commands: exit, env.
.IP \[bu] 2
Simple error handling.
.SH USAGE
In interactive mode:
.PP
Start the shell and type commands, followed by the Enter key.
.PP
In non-interactive mode:
.PP
Pipe commands into the shell from echo or a script.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Running ls in interactive mode:
.RS 4
$> ./simple_shell
.br
$> ls -l
.RE
.PP
Running ls in non-interactive mode:
.RS 4
$> echo "ls -l" | ./simple_shell
.RE
.SH AUTHORS
Jonathan Huybrechts and Jérémy Carpentier.
.SH SEE ALSO
.B sh(1), bash(1)
